Ombrage was walking by the river, book in hand, and sat under a tree near the water. After what has been happening lately, she needed some time alone, some time to think and just *relax*, even if it was hard. 
She took a deep breath and was just looking around, writting whatever came to her mind.
“Ooooooo! What have we here..?” a sudden loud, dramatic voice questioned, Illuvies bent over, arms crossed behind his back with a wide, curious smile on his face.

Ombrage let out a surprised squeak, and half of her body instantly turned into a shadow. She slowly turned her head to see who was the voice she heard, and asked, with a slightly shaking voice "W...who are you ?..."

A head tilt and a bright smile was all he changed. “Oh, silly me, I’ve been caught again! Sorry, my dear— if I announce my name, it’ll mess up the whole story! You don’t want to have silly ol’ me change anything, do ya? But if you want to call me anything, call me white!”
She stared at him, confused, *what was he talking about?* "I... alright... White" Her body went back to its normal form, and she stood up, still a bit shaken. " What do you mean by 'story'?"

“Did I say that? I just keep slipping and slipping more and more thoughts out, huh? I should really zip my mouth shut!” he jokes, pinching the side of his mouth and bringing it across, his mouth suddenly looking like a closed zipper. After a moment, the zipper look disappears. “Say, you’re a lot less *hostile* than the last mun I spooked! You’re like a scared little pup compared to her!”

Ombrage just kept staring at him in confusion, *that sure is a strange individual*... She held her book close to her chest, and put her pen in her hair. She tilted her head "I... thank you I guess ?.... I don't really like violence... So I prefer to not be hostile I guess"

“Not to say I do not enjoy having a civil conversation with someone, but what’s the *fun* in being *calm* all the time? Don’t you just want to *roughen up* sometimes?” he asks, balling up his hands into fists and playfully punching the air like a boxer.

She looked away for a moment, she *did* want to sometimes, a *lot*, but she could never managed herself to do so "Well, I mean, I do, I would be liying to say I didn't at least once, but... I'm not that kind of person, I'm pretty weak anyway" she awkardly laughed, playing with her hands

“Oh? But I don’t sense weakness at all, my dear! The only thing I sense in you is *potential!* You hold yourself back! Give me a moment, if you will,” he asks, swiftly lifting his large scarf over his head, the parts clipped to his sides unclipping as if like magic. It fades to glittery dust before it can hit the ground. He shakes his head a little, the large, white curls bouncing as he does, and he stretches a bit. “My, it’s been *ages* since I took off that old thing!” he exclaims, hearing cracks in the unused bones. He turns to Ombrage again and smiles, predator-like.
“Well, come now, show me what you’ve got!”

Ombrage was unsure, she looked at the stranger prepare and was panicking a little, she put her book down and and shook her head "W-wait! are you... are you sure about this ? I mean, I don't fight *much* and even if I have *'potential'* I don't want to hurt anybody! " She was very much scared of Illuvies, and wanted to avoid fighting at all cost, his smile just... did not put her at ease. Despite that, she summoned her stand, who took the shape of a knight-like armor, but with a very dark gray as a color. If he was going to attack, she would at least be protected.

“Of course I’m sure! Look at me, dear, do you think I’d start this if I wasn’t sure we were both safe?” he asked, spreading out his arms. To put it into perspective, Plasma are a bit bigger than muns, so he’s about... say, 16’? Just as an average-sized Plasma. “So then, what are you waiting for, my dear?”

She took a deep breath, it was the first time someone was so... open to fight her, surely it's fine if they ask for it, right? no reason to feel guilty. She was still intimidated by the plasma, both by height and by the way he was acting. 
After losing herself in her thoughts for a few seconds, she took out a scythe from the shadows, and she then vanished in the shadow of the tree.She appeared again, right behind Illuvies, with her scythe ready to strike, but she stopped herself right before hitting him.

He whipped around right as she appeared, gripping the scythe with two fingers and smiling, before pouting at the realization that she stopped before she could hit him. “You have so much potential, *so much!* But you lack commitment! If this is to be a *proper* fight, you must be *committed* to the action!”
He shoves her off, backing up again. “Come on, then! Fight like you mean it!”

Ombrage was surprised he managed to grab it that easly, maybe she had underestimated his strengh. His words were... strangely flattering, she never thought she had potential. She stumbled a bit as he shoved her off, but quickly regain balance before metturing to herself *"Alright"*. 
She ran straight towards him, this time, only fading into a shadow in front of him to reappear to his side, this time, striking without holding back.

He dodged backwards, able to sense the emotions she held, growing more and more fiery with each and every step— he *loved* it! She was realizing her strength! This feeling— *all* these feelings— they were incredible!
“Bravo! *Bravo!* You’re beginning to understand! Now the fun can *truly* begin!”
He took a few hefty steps back before bringing his hands up to his head, smoothing the long curls back and tying them with.. A hair band? When did he get that? Pulling out a single, curled strand from the tight ponytail, he shook his head from side to side and held out a hand, almost as if he wanted her to grab onto it.
“Come on snake, *let’s rattle!*”

She didn't expect him to dodge it that easly, he was*good* but strangely enough, this only motivated her to strike again, and again, until at least one land. She was being *congratulated* for once. She put the visor of her armor down, a faint smile across her face. 
Once her opponent finished preparing, she ran straight to him, striking multiple times at a rather impressive speed, trying to hit him.

*Oh this is thrilling! This is ABSOLUTELY thrilling!* he thought to himself, dodging from side to side, but still letting her nick him with the blade, golden blood spillling out of the wounds and onto the grass below him. “You’re incredible! This speed is almost akin to mine— Keep striking! You’re bound to land soon!”
*If she can land a strike on me without letting her... My, this might be the first I’ve ever seen to happen! Go, Ombrage, go!*

After a few more strikes, she started to notice the blood, thinking about stopping, but her opponent's encouragements pushed her to strike more. She never felt this... *burning* feeling, this will to fight, she didn't want to admit it but she never felt more... *alive*. *This is... fun!* she thought to herself, thinking on how she could land a good strike. 
Suddenly, she vanished in the shadows again, and appeared in his back, repeating her multiple strike technique.

He had been so caught up in his excitement that he had almost forgotten about her shadow ability, thought not completely. He had moved from side to side, but had not turned around, instead opting to launch himself forward, to a tree, and then launching himself off of it, spinning like a drill and heading towards her at lightning speed. *You can attack so well, but can you defend?*

She had a wider grin on her face, while he managed to avoid her attacks, this only fueled her. She was startled by his spinning, and instinctively turned into a shadow, although she was a bit slow, she managed to avoid most of the damage.
“Well, that’s a *tad* bit disappointing. Come on, girl, show me you can *move!*” he yells, launching himself again, letting her prepare this time with his announcement.
This time, she was prepared. She turned into a shadow to dodge the attack, and hide in Illuvies's shadow. Once he stopped spinning, she waited a bit before striking again.

When he had slowed his spinning, yanking his legs in front of him to land, he gasped loudly as he felt the strike on his back, ripping through his clothes and leaving a large, shining golden cut throughout the large of his back. He stumbled a bit, but flipped, ultimately catching himself on all fours, holding up a hand to stretch it out and balance himself. He panted for a moment, before standing up, reaching a hand behind his back and pulling it to his front, playing with the golden fluid inbetween his fingers.

He was quiet for a moment.
“You.. struck me. You managed to strike me.”

Ombrage froze *she did it*, she managed to stike him, and it wasn't a small one either. 
She was speechless, on one hand, she felt proud but on the other, she did *hurt* someone. After a moment she took off her visor, a concerned look on her face, she was back to her usual shy self. 
"S...Sorry-" is all she could mutter.

“You’re...” he mumbled, before turning around and stretching his arms out, the biggest, proudest smile on his face he could ever hope to muster. “**INCREDIBLE**! YOU’RE ABSOLUTELY INCREDIBLE!” 
He launched himself forward as fast as he could and caught her in a hug, swinging her around and throwing her into the air before catching her again and hugging her tightly.

“YOU’RE SPECTACULAR! Nobody has *ever* even come *CLOSE* to marking me before, yet you’ve done it in merely a MINUTE! The potential you have was already astonishing, but now it’s growing higher and higher to *ever before!*”

She let out a surprised scream, not expecting the hug, and *certainly* not being thrown in the air. This stranger was certainly the most... *bizarre* person she ever met. "Uuuuuuh... t-thanks?...." She couldn't say anything else, she had *way* too many thoughts running through her head. She was extremly flattered, and her already yellow shining cheeks were brighter. 
She didn't expect to be praised, *especially* for that, but she was glad he wasn't mad.
“Oh honey of *course* I’m not mad! You are by far have some of the MOST potential I have ever FELT! My, I thought *Gemi* was incredible— you pass her by *lightyears!*”

*Wait* She never said she thought he was mad, how did he figure it out ? She shook her head, not wanting to focus on that. She had a genuine smile was on her face "I... I'm flattered... thank you. I don't fight much, most of my experience comes from the times I was on earth, to be honest"

“All the more impressive! You should wear your confidence on your sleeves more often, it’s very attractive!” he suggests, putting her down and patting her head approvingly. “Anyone who knows you should feel lucky they do! I know *I* sure do!”
"Oh, uh, I guess you're right" her armor disapeared and she scratched her neck " I...I don't think many people even *knows* me, honestly." she shrugged

“Then *make yourself known!* Go out there, *show* those who doubt you what you’re made of! You can *never* go wrong when you have skill like yours, my dear!” he says, cupping Ombrage’s chin and tilting her face up towards him.

She looked away, shyly "Well... Fighting isn't the *only* thing important, right? I'm not the social butterfly type...but I guess I can try!" She really didn't like to make herself known, she did enjoy the silent of being alone, but it does get lonely sometimes...
“Hm... If I am correct, there is a revolution going on? Against the council.. Whose side will you be on?” he asks, curious, as he sits down in front of the river, patting a spot next to him.

She stood silent before sitting next to him "I.... I don't know.... I'm really not feeling this revolution, honestly, people will be hurt, and I'm hoping i can stop that" She paused for a bit, lost in her thoughts, before continuing "There was... an attempt at solving things peacefully, but I'm unsure if it'll work out"
“Well, go with your heart, I suppose. Who do you believe will come out on top?”

She went silent for a bit "Well, I'll be honest, I think it's the plasma... they're extremly powerful afterall... I don't think all of us could beat them" *but I do want us to win* she thought. Despite how scared she was of the plasma, she dreamt of a world where she didn't have to *destroy* and only the plasma were stopping her dream.

“...You believe the Plasma will win, yet you hope with all your heart that the revolution will. Then, I suppose it’s only wise to go with who you wish to side with, am I wrong?”
As this point, his clothes has fixed itself up and the mark, although not gone, has been dried, covered by his scarf, which reformed on his body soon after he sat down.

"Wait...." Ombrage was speechless yet again, so he *was* reading her mind all this time *is he...a plasma?* she should've seen this coming, from his height to how strong he was, but somehow it didn't click until now 
"You..you're a plasma?" her voice was shaking.
“What do you believe, my dear?”

"Well, I'm guessing you *are* a plasma" She let out a sigh and put her head in her hands "I honestly don't know anymore...Everything has been going so fast, I'm just...lost I guess" 
Despite the fact that he seemed to be a plasma, Ombrage did feel more comfortable, he wasn't as intimidating as the others

“I’m glad you don’t find me intimidating, my dear. Though.. I suppose usually I do, but you’re a special case,” he shrugs, allowing himself to find comfort in the sound of the river. “It is perfectly fine to feel lost. Many people can when it comes to war— helps them realize many things. It’s the best thing about it, if you ask for my artistic opinion.”
He turns to her, eyes glowing. “Do not be afraid to explore every option. *Unlock your story*, my love, and perhaps you will find what you are looking for.”

She sighed again, laying down, looking at the sky "I guess you're right... Although, I would've prefer that none of this happened in the first place...I liked it when it was peaceful...Guess I'll make the most out of it" 
She paused and glance at Illuvies "What about *you*, what are you even doing in the first place ? I've never seen you around for sure..."

“...To be truthful to the fullest extent, I never thought I’d come back here in the first place,” he muses dipping a finger in the river and swirling designs into the flowing water carelessly. “It was boring. The council was no *fun.* The most entertainment I had had in *centuries* was what we did to that child, but Binyamin and Bun refused to let me do it again, so I left. I only came back because.. Well, about a week ago, this world was *blooming* with emotion like never before!”
He threw his hands up in the air, smiling. “It *excited* me! I was *thrilled!* I rushed back here as soon as possible, to find the muns have *revolted!* It’s incredible! You’ve all come so far!”

Ombrage sat up, intrested, she'd never thought that a *plasma* would leave like that, and that the council sounded like a game, almost "What... what did you *do* to that child ?... Is this some kind of game to you?..."
“I’ve said this before, but I prefer to call it a *show*. I *strive* for drama, you see. Do you know a child by the name of ‘Polaris’?” he asks, turning to face Ombrage.
She froze, she *definitly* heard that name before *the meeting* it was there that she saw him  "So...A show...uh ? Yes, I think I've seen him once..."

“That child... Oh, how silly he was. When Morise introduced him as their newest experiment, I was *not* thrilled. I *hated* what Morise did to the children. Reduced them to nothing but emotionless *shells.* It *completely* squandered their potential. But Polaris.. his experiment was *different.* No removal of emotions. Just complete and total isolation. I could sense a revolt from lightyears away,” he began, smiling at the memories of it all.

Ombrage was listening carefully, a look of disgust on her face, *so it's true..;.* she tought. Total Isolation sounded awful, she started to understand why Shale and Polaris were so angry. "Yeah... I can see that" she muttered

“And right I was! You should have *seen* the way he *stormed* into the council room, *DEMANDING* we give him answers! He reminded me of Jotaro now more than he ever will after GER was done with him!” he laughed out, standing up and twirling around.
"Wait.... Did you say...." She took a moment to process what he said "So, Polaris is Jotaro's mun ? Who's that GER ?...."

“Mhm! Seeing that child now, it’s hard to ever imagine he’d call his own *mother* a bitch! In fact, I wonder where that silly mun is— Holly’s mun, I mean. She was completely removed from the picture once Morise got involved with her child!”
Ombrage covered her mouth in shock, he was saying all of this... With such a *cheerful* tone, she had no words.

“Oh come, now— why the long face? You know he couldn’t have gotten so terrified of his own shadow from *nothing*, am I right? He used to be so *brave!* That was about........ Hm, if he is 1,700,00 years at least, then it was about... 1,300,000 years ago? He was very intelligent for his age!”
Her face went from disgusted to furious and scared "What...what did you *do* to him ?...***why?***"

“Oh, it wasn’t *my* idea! At least not at first!” he mused, placing a finger to his chin and looking to the sky absentmindedly. “Morise wanted to put him into his ‘place’, whatever that ominous message meant, and thought they could only do it by force of *fear.* An exciting concept, really! My, you should’ve seen his face when I told Binyamin to go fetch Helio! I told Morise I had a *grand* idea and they were compliant *instantly!* The fear in that boy’s eyes— ooooo I just *knew* I had made the right decision!”

Ombrage felt like she was about to throw up, her mind was coming up with so many things that could've happened, and she did *not* want to think about any of them. She felt bad for Polaris, she felt bad for even *attempting* to defend Morise. She couldn't bring herself to say anything.

“My, the pure *disgust* that Helio boy felt on that day was just the cherry on top! You should’ve seen how warped his face became once Polaris started screaming! We had full view of what he was going through, too! Oh, it was *fantastic!* So bloody, so gory, so *dramatic!*” he hugged himself, smiling wide at the memories.

Her mind was screaming *SHUT UP* over and over, she couldn't handle how he was speaking about this, people were in *pain* and he was just here, laughing and smiling. She suddenly took out her scythe, and in a pure rage, attempt to strike him.

He grabbed at her grip on the scythe and pulled her arm back, linking his other hand with *her* other hand, standing in a position not unsimilar to how you would dance. “My dear, you may have landed a strike on me once, but believe me, when it comes to your rage, I am the person who you give yourself away to most.”
She shivered, she was *fuming* with rage, and turned into a shadow to avoid Illuvies's grip, appearing again a few steps away from him. She wasn't saying a word.

“Oh, why have you gone silent, my dear? Did my riling you up not give away that I may not have the most *innocent* tendencies? My apologies,” he bows, “I should have made it clear from the beginning— I feed off of the heavy emotions of others. The taste of fear and anger are some of the more *delicious* emotions.”
He cracks an eye open, peering at her with the pure white orb. *And you, my dear, are giving me a full course meal.*

Her face slowly turned to a  blank expression, despite how much she was *boiling* inside, she tried to keep her calm "Once again, I was a fool. But at least now I know I guess. You're disgusting" 
This was probably the first time she was so honest while talking to someone, maybe because it was also the first time she has been so angered in *ages*. She kept standing where she was, despite how much she wanted to attack him

*Ooo.. She’s growing.. This is impressive.*
“I wouldn’t call myself *disgusting*, perse.. I just feed off of the fears of others! Besides, Polaris is the only child I was okay with traumatizing. Although I did enjoy Helio’s *pure fear*, I didn’t enjoy hurting him as much. He was so much younger..”
For the first time, Illuvies frowned. He was upset.

Though, that changed quickly. He waved his hand back and forth, relaxing his expression again. “No matter, though! And you are no fool. The only foolish thing you are doing is masking your anger. You may hide it from others, Ombrage, but not me. I can *sense* your hatred for me at the core of your heart.”

He began walking forward.

"... feeding off other people's fears *is* disgusting... And you still were *ok* with it " she was speaking firmly. She took a deep breath, tried her best to relax, but every words Illuvies would say made her rage stronger. 
As she saw Illuvies take a step forward, she took one back, even if she hit him *once* she wasn't sure she could do it for longer. She was starting to get *tired*, both physically and mentally.

He continued his strides.
*Crunch. Crunch. Crunch.* His feet crushed the leaves on the ground below him, and as he continued forward, he smiled at her, innocent and small. “My dear, dear Ombrage. Tell me, why do you think I feed off of emotions? Why they are my strongest sense?”

She kept going backwards, occasionally looking back in order to not fall. 
"Oh, I don't know, because you're a sick person with a twisted moral compass ?" her voice was sharp, she was sick of his games.

“...”
He stayed quiet. She was about to back into the stream, anyways.
...And he was right, she wasn't being carful enough, and ended up tripping and falling in the stream. Once she got back to her senses, she grabbed the ledge to get out of the water

“Oh, my dear. My poor, dear, naive Ombrage...” 
He knelt down, grabbing her face forcefully with one hand, the grip tight and unforgiving.
“Why, young one, do you believe I search for others fears? Hopes? Loves? What makes them scream in joy and what makes them scream in sadness?”
He smiled, his expression almost.. sad. 
“It is because they are not mine to feel.”
With that, he lets go, calmly standing up and backing away a few steps. The next choice would be hers.

She was hating the way he spoke to her, and how he hold her face, with his *disguting* hands. Although she was boiling, she felt a little bit of pity for him. Not having emotions must be... *strange*, but this didn't justify anything. 
She got back on her feet, she rushed to him in a last attempt to wound him, but she was tired, and she clearly was slower.

He sighed. Long and hard
“You know, I’d rather not *truly* fight you, Ombrage.”
He took a step forward, gripping her wrists to hold her still.
“The thrill of it all is all I can experience. It’s upsetting how much you despise me for this.”

She was panting, she tried to fight back to get out of his grip, but she couldn't. 
" You....You *willingly* hurt someone... I... I can't *understand* how someone else's fear can be so... great"

“I understand. You are not me, just as I am not you. You do not know what it feels like to me.”
He kneels down, all the way to the grass, forcing her to sit down all the same, keeping her lower than him.
She sat down, and eventually her scythe vanished in a shadow "Yes, I don't know what it feels like to you, but I believe that there's lines that *shouldn't* be crossed"
“I see... Say, how does it feel when you’ve gone a day without food? Perhaps, two days? Three? Mayhaps even a week?” he asked, tilting his head.
"...." she paused, slightly confused, before answering " It feels...bad... like your whole body is about to collapse...and it's slowly consuming itself"

“Then how do you think it would feel for me, one who feeds on emotions, to have a *fantastic* dinner. Three entire meals in one sitting, and then to go without any food for.. Say, around 1,300,000 years?”
"... Bad...Very Bad"  she was trying to think about a counter argument *something* to say, but her mind just went blank. It *would* feel awful.

“Then tell me, young Ombrage, would it be fair to keep anyone starving for that long? To keep them *so close* to the food they so desperately need and desire, only for it to dwindle down into nothing *thousands* upon *millions* of times?”
"I....no, it wouldn't...but, isn't there another way?..."

“I’m afraid not, my dear Ombrage. The only feelings I will ever even hope to muster are the desire to feed and the thrill of the action. The potential you showed today completely squandered my hunger— thank you.”
He gave her another smile, small and innocent and *lying.*
Though, it’s not like she’d be able to tell.

She let out a long sigh, giving up on reasoning with him, there was no way she could. 
She just stared at him, blankly, she was hoping that at least it meant he wouldn't hurt anyone for a while.

“...I believe I’ve overstayed my welcome,” he says after a moment, letting go of her face and standing up straight, wiping some dirt off of his sleeves. “You were a wonder to fight, my dear, but I best be heading off, lest someone comes looking for you.”
"...finally" she muttered, after he let go of her face. She layed on the ground, too tired to move.

“Oh! By the way, Ombrage..”
Suddenly, in less than the blink of an eye, his face was to hers, eyes wide and threatening, the white orbs almost looking as if they are spinning a thousand miles a minute.
“I’d *prefer* to stay *hidden.* Gemi refused to keep that promise, can I hope you will not do the same?”
Ombrage shivered and looked away, but nodded "I... I promise, I promise I will" She was to scared to say no

He closed his eyes and smiled, pleased with the answer.
“Good. Tatah~”

He disappears.
Ombrage let out a sigh of relief *finally, she could rest*. Her eye closed and she fell asleep.
